[
    {
        "text": "Turkish tea drinking is a bit different than the customs we know from England at 4:30,...",
        "startTime": 597,
        "endTime": 5569,
        "slowStartTime": 1046,
        "slowEndTime": 8579
    },
    {
        "text": "...or the elaborate ritual of the tea ceremony in Japan.",
        "startTime": 6126,
        "endTime": 9149,
        "slowStartTime": 9339,
        "slowEndTime": 13948
    },
    {
        "text": "It is less complicated and very straightforward, kind of like the Turks themselves.",
        "startTime": 10141,
        "endTime": 14427,
        "slowStartTime": 15361,
        "slowEndTime": 21865
    },
    {
        "text": "Get your glass poured, you plunk in one or two sugars according to your taste,...",
        "startTime": 16695,
        "endTime": 23165,
        "slowStartTime": 25192,
        "slowEndTime": 34973
    },
    {
        "text": "Take your spoon, stir it. Make a lot of noise with that spoon, a lot of noise.",
        "startTime": 23748,
        "endTime": 29273,
        "slowStartTime": 35772,
        "slowEndTime": 44135
    },
    {
        "text": "Hold it by the edge because it's very, very hot.",
        "startTime": 32833,
        "endTime": 35338,
        "slowStartTime": 49400,
        "slowEndTime": 53232
    },
    {
        "text": "Sip very slowly...",
        "startTime": 36029,
        "endTime": 37412,
        "slowStartTime": 54194,
        "slowEndTime": 56343
    },
    {
        "text": "...because it's hot and also because you're going to have to drink several of these glasses.",
        "startTime": 39285,
        "endTime": 45121,
        "slowStartTime": 59077,
        "slowEndTime": 67907
    },
    {
        "text": "Just like potato chips, you just can't have one,...",
        "startTime": 46209,
        "endTime": 48768,
        "slowStartTime": 69463,
        "slowEndTime": 73377
    },
    {
        "text": "...for etiquette requires that at least three be served to you.",
        "startTime": 49082,
        "endTime": 51920,
        "slowStartTime": 73773,
        "slowEndTime": 78105
    },
    {
        "text": "So, that means you're going to be drinking a lot of tea in Turkey, at all hours of the day.",
        "startTime": 53353,
        "endTime": 58817,
        "slowStartTime": 80179,
        "slowEndTime": 88450
    },
    {
        "text": "So, as I said, in my eyes, this little glass of tea is the symbol of all of Turkey.",
        "startTime": 60430,
        "endTime": 65614,
        "slowStartTime": 90795,
        "slowEndTime": 98646
    },
    {
        "text": "Turkish tea is ruby red.",
        "startTime": 69937,
        "endTime": 71327,
        "slowStartTime": 105055,
        "slowEndTime": 107215
    },
    {
        "text": "Not black or green, but red.",
        "startTime": 72581,
        "endTime": 75395,
        "slowStartTime": 109021,
        "slowEndTime": 113317
    },
    {
        "text": "Red is the spirit of patriotic blood flowing in the heart of every Turk.",
        "startTime": 76339,
        "endTime": 79884,
        "slowStartTime": 114658,
        "slowEndTime": 120051
    },
    {
        "text": "Red is their flag they wave with great pride.",
        "startTime": 80636,
        "endTime": 83272,
        "slowStartTime": 121104,
        "slowEndTime": 125133
    },
    {
        "text": "Red is the rich wool of the colorful carpets they weave.",
        "startTime": 84026,
        "endTime": 87015,
        "slowStartTime": 126189,
        "slowEndTime": 130747
    },
    {
        "text": "Red is the dancing tulips of their spring time meadows.",
        "startTime": 87600,
        "endTime": 90725,
        "slowStartTime": 131550,
        "slowEndTime": 136312
    },
    {
        "text": "The form of those tulips is reflected in the very shape of the tea glass itself.",
        "startTime": 91261,
        "endTime": 97067,
        "slowStartTime": 137042,
        "slowEndTime": 145825
    }
]